  <description type="morphology">Stems erect, 3–4 dm. Leaves proximalmost alternate, distal ones short petiolate;
        blade ovate or ovate-elliptic to deltoid, 6–50 × 4–40 mm, margin entire or repand-dentate,
        grayish scurfy when young. Fruiting bracteoles sessile or some stipitate (stipe 0.5–5 mm),
        cuneate to obovate to suborbicular in profile, 3.8–11.2 × 4–8.8(–14) mm, usually compressed,
        united nearly to apex, green free margin extending nearly to base, dentate, sides smooth or
        sparsely to densely tuberculate or cristate. 2n = 18.</description>
